  106. ‌let size_expr (env:environment) exp =
  107.   let rec size localenv = function
  108.       Cconst_int _ | Cconst_natint _ -> Arch.size_int
  109.     | Cconst_symbol _ ->
  110.         Arch.size_addr
  111.     | Cconst_float _ -> Arch.size_float
  112.     | Cvar id ->
  113.         begin try
  114.           V.Map.find id localenv
  115.         with Not_found ->
  116.         try
  117.           let regs = env_find id env in
  118.           size_machtype (Array.map (fun r -> r.typ) regs)
  119.         with Not_found ->
  120.           Misc.fatal_error("Selection.size_expr: unbound var " ^
  121.                            V.unique_name id)
  122.         end
  123.     | Ctuple el ->
  124.         List.fold_right (fun e sz -> size localenv e + sz) el 0
  125.     | Cop(op, _, _) ->
  126.         size_machtype(oper_result_type op)
  127.     | Clet(id, arg, body) ->
  128.         size (V.Map.add (VP.var id) (size localenv arg) localenv) body
  129.     | Csequence(_e1, e2) ->
  130.         size localenv e2
  131.     | _ ->
  132.         Misc.fatal_error "Selection.size_expr"
  133.   in size V.Map.empty exp

  162. (* "Join" two instruction sequences, making sure they return their results
  163.    in the same registers. *)

  165. ‌let join env opt_r1 seq1 opt_r2 seq2 =
  166.   match (opt_r1, opt_r2) with
  167.     (None, _) -> opt_r2
  168.   | (_, None) -> opt_r1
  169.   | (Some r1, Some r2) ->
  170.       let l1 = Array.length r1 in
  171.       assert (l1 = Array.length r2);
  172.       let r = Array.make l1 Reg.dummy in
  173.       for i = 0 to l1-1 do
  174.         if Reg.anonymous r1.(i)
  175.           && Cmm.ge_component r1.(i).typ r2.(i).typ
  176.         then begin
  177.           r.(i) <- r1.(i);
  178.           seq2#insert_move env r2.(i) r1.(i)
  179.         end else if Reg.anonymous r2.(i)
  180.           && Cmm.ge_component r2.(i).typ r1.(i).typ
  181.         then begin
  182.           r.(i) <- r2.(i);
  183.           seq1#insert_move env r1.(i) r2.(i)
  184.         end else begin
  185.           let typ = Cmm.lub_component r1.(i).typ r2.(i).typ in
  186.           r.(i) <- Reg.create typ;
  187.           seq1#insert_move env r1.(i) r.(i);
  188.           seq2#insert_move env r2.(i) r.(i)
  189.         end
  190.       done;
  191.       Some r

  193. (* Same, for N branches *)

  195. ‌let join_array env rs =
  196.   let some_res = ref None in
  197.   for i = 0 to Array.length rs - 1 do
  198.     let (r, _) = rs.(i) in
  199.     match r with
  200.     | None -> ()
  201.     | Some r ->
  202.       match !some_res with
  203.       | None -> some_res := Some (r, Array.map (fun r -> r.typ) r)
  204.       | Some (r', types) ->
  205.         let types =
  206.           Array.map2 (fun r typ -> Cmm.lub_component r.typ typ) r types
  207.         in
  208.         some_res := Some (r', types)
  209.   done;
  210.   match !some_res with
  211.     None -> None
  212.   | Some (template, types) ->
  213.       let size_res = Array.length template in
  214.       let res = Array.make size_res Reg.dummy in
  215.       for i = 0 to size_res - 1 do
  216.         res.(i) <- Reg.create types.(i)
  217.       done;
  218.       for i = 0 to Array.length rs - 1 do
  219.         let (r, s) = rs.(i) in
  220.         match r with
  221.           None -> ()
  222.         | Some r -> s#insert_moves env r res
  223.       done;
  224.       Some res

  265. module Effect_and_coeffect : sig
  266.   type t

  268.   val none : t
  269.   val arbitrary : t

  271.   val effect : t -> Effect.t
  272.   val coeffect : t -> Coeffect.t

  274.   val pure_and_copure : t -> bool

  276.   val effect_only : Effect.t -> t
  277.   val coeffect_only : Coeffect.t -> t

  279.   val join : t -> t -> t
  280.   val join_list_map : 'a list -> ('a -> t) -> t
  281. end = struct
  282. ‌  type t = Effect.t * Coeffect.t

  284. ‌  let none = Effect.None, Coeffect.None
  285. ‌  let arbitrary = Effect.Arbitrary, Coeffect.Arbitrary

  287. ‌  let effect (e, _ce) = e
  288. ‌  let coeffect (_e, ce) = ce

  290. ‌  let pure_and_copure (e, ce) = Effect.pure e && Coeffect.copure ce

  292. ‌  let effect_only e = e, Coeffect.None
  293. ‌  let coeffect_only ce = Effect.None, ce

  295. ‌  let join (e1, ce1) (e2, ce2) =
  296.     Effect.join e1 e2, Coeffect.join ce1 ce2

  298. ‌  let join_list_map xs f =
  299.     match xs with
  300.     | [] -> none
  301.     | x::xs -> List.fold_left (fun acc x -> join acc (f x)) (f x) xs
  302. end

  304. (* The default instruction selection class *)

  306. class virtual selector_generic = object (self)

  308. (* A syntactic criterion used in addition to judgements about (co)effects as
  309.    to whether the evaluation of a given expression may be deferred by
  310.    [emit_parts].  This criterion is a property of the instruction selection
  311.    algorithm in this file rather than a property of the Cmm language.
  312. *)
  313. method is_simple_expr = function
  314.     Cconst_int _ -> true
  315.   | Cconst_natint _ -> true
  316.   | Cconst_float _ -> true
  317.   | Cconst_symbol _ -> true
  318.   | Cvar _ -> true
  319.   | Ctuple el -> List.for_all self#is_simple_expr el
  320.   | Clet(_id, arg, body) | Clet_mut(_id, _, arg, body) ->
  321.     self#is_simple_expr arg && self#is_simple_expr body
  322.   | Cphantom_let(_var, _defining_expr, body) -> self#is_simple_expr body
  323.   | Csequence(e1, e2) -> self#is_simple_expr e1 && self#is_simple_expr e2
  324.   | Cop(op, args, _) ->
  325.       begin match op with
  326.         (* The following may have side effects *)
  327.       | Capply _ | Cextcall _ | Calloc | Cstore _ | Craise _ | Copaque -> false
  328.         (* The remaining operations are simple if their args are *)
  329.       | Cload _ | Caddi | Csubi | Cmuli | Cmulhi | Cdivi | Cmodi | Cand | Cor
  330.       | Cxor | Clsl | Clsr | Casr | Ccmpi _ | Caddv | Cadda | Ccmpa _ | Cnegf
  331.       | Cabsf | Caddf | Csubf | Cmulf | Cdivf | Cfloatofint | Cintoffloat
  332.       | Ccmpf _ | Ccheckbound | Cdls_get ->
  333.           List.for_all self#is_simple_expr args
  334.       end
  335.   | Cassign _ | Cifthenelse _ | Cswitch _ | Ccatch _ | Cexit _
  336.   | Ctrywith _ -> false

  338. (* Analyses the effects and coeffects of an expression.  This is used across
  339.    a whole list of expressions with a view to determining which expressions
  340.    may have their evaluation deferred.  The result of this function, modulo
  341.    target-specific judgements if the [effects_of] method is overridden, is a
  342.    property of the Cmm language rather than anything particular about the
  343.    instruction selection algorithm in this file.

  345.    In the case of e.g. an OCaml function call, the arguments whose evaluation
  346.    cannot be deferred (cf. [emit_parts], below) are computed in right-to-left
  347.    order first with their results going into temporaries, then the block is
  348.    allocated, then the remaining arguments are evaluated before being
  349.    combined with the temporaries. *)
  350. method effects_of exp =
  351.   let module EC = Effect_and_coeffect in
  352.   match exp with
  353.   | Cconst_int _ | Cconst_natint _ | Cconst_float _ | Cconst_symbol _
  354.   | Cvar _ -> EC.none
  355.   | Ctuple el -> EC.join_list_map el self#effects_of
  356.   | Clet (_id, arg, body) | Clet_mut (_id, _, arg, body) ->
  357.     EC.join (self#effects_of arg) (self#effects_of body)
  358.   | Cphantom_let (_var, _defining_expr, body) -> self#effects_of body
  359.   | Csequence (e1, e2) ->
  360.     EC.join (self#effects_of e1) (self#effects_of e2)
  361.   | Cifthenelse (cond, _ifso_dbg, ifso, _ifnot_dbg, ifnot, _dbg) ->
  362.     EC.join (self#effects_of cond)
  363.       (EC.join (self#effects_of ifso) (self#effects_of ifnot))
  364.   | Cop (op, args, _) ->
  365. ‌    let from_op =
  366.       match op with
  367.       | Capply _ | Cextcall _ | Copaque -> EC.arbitrary
  368.       | Calloc -> EC.none
  369.       | Cstore _ -> EC.effect_only Effect.Arbitrary
  370.       | Craise _ | Ccheckbound -> EC.effect_only Effect.Raise
  371.       | Cload {mutability = Asttypes.Immutable} -> EC.none
  372.       | Cload {mutability = Asttypes.Mutable} | Cdls_get ->
  373.           EC.coeffect_only Coeffect.Read_mutable
  374.       | Caddi | Csubi | Cmuli | Cmulhi | Cdivi | Cmodi | Cand | Cor | Cxor
  375.       | Clsl | Clsr | Casr | Ccmpi _ | Caddv | Cadda | Ccmpa _ | Cnegf | Cabsf
  376.       | Caddf | Csubf | Cmulf | Cdivf | Cfloatofint | Cintoffloat | Ccmpf _ ->
  377.         EC.none
  378.     in
  379.     EC.join from_op (EC.join_list_map args self#effects_of)
  380.   | Cassign _ | Cswitch _ | Ccatch _ | Cexit _ | Ctrywith _ ->
  381.     EC.arbitrary

  406. (* call marking methods, documented in selectgen.mli *)
  407. val contains_calls = ref false

  409. method mark_call =
  410.   contains_calls := true

  412. method mark_tailcall = ()

  414. method mark_c_tailcall =
  415.   if !Clflags.debug then contains_calls := true

  417. method mark_instr = function
  418.   | Iop (Icall_ind | Icall_imm _ | Iextcall _) ->
  419.       self#mark_call
  420.   | Iop (Itailcall_ind | Itailcall_imm _) ->
  421.       self#mark_tailcall
  422.   | Iop (Ialloc _) | Iop (Ipoll _) ->
  423.       self#mark_call (* caml_alloc*, caml_garbage_collection (incl. polls) *)
  424.   | Iop (Iintop (Icheckbound) | Iintop_imm(Icheckbound, _)) ->
  425.       self#mark_c_tailcall (* caml_ml_array_bound_error *)
  426.   | Iraise raise_kind ->
  427.     begin match raise_kind with
  428.       | Lambda.Raise_notrace -> ()
  429.       | Lambda.Raise_regular
  430.       | Lambda.Raise_reraise ->
  431.           (* PR#6239 *)
  432.         (* caml_stash_backtrace; we #mark_call rather than
  433.            #mark_c_tailcall to get a good stack backtrace *)
  434.           self#mark_call
  435.     end
  436.   | Itrywith _ ->
  437.     self#mark_call
  438.   | _ -> ()

  440. (* Default instruction selection for operators *)

  442. method select_operation op args _dbg =
  443.   match (op, args) with
  444.   | (Capply _, Cconst_symbol (func, _dbg) :: rem) ->
  445.     (Icall_imm { func; }, rem)
  446.   | (Capply _, _) ->
  447.     (Icall_ind, args)
  448.   | (Cextcall(func, ty_res, ty_args, alloc), _) ->
  449.     Iextcall { func; alloc; ty_res; ty_args; stack_ofs = -1}, args
  450.   | (Cload {memory_chunk; mutability; is_atomic}, [arg]) ->
  451.       let (addressing_mode, eloc) = self#select_addressing memory_chunk arg in
  452.       (Iload {memory_chunk; addressing_mode; mutability; is_atomic}, [eloc])
  453.   | (Cstore (chunk, init), [arg1; arg2]) ->
  454.       let (addr, eloc) = self#select_addressing chunk arg1 in
  455.       let is_assign =
  456.         match init with
  457.         | Lambda.Root_initialization -> false
  458.         | Lambda.Heap_initialization -> false
  459.         | Lambda.Assignment -> true
  460.       in
  461.       if chunk = Word_int || chunk = Word_val then begin
  462.         let (op, newarg2) = self#select_store is_assign addr arg2 in
  463.         (op, [newarg2; eloc])
  464.       end else begin
  465.         (Istore(chunk, addr, is_assign), [arg2; eloc])
  466.         (* Inversion addr/datum in Istore *)
  467.       end
  468.   | (Cdls_get, _) -> Idls_get, args
  469.   | (Calloc, _) -> (Ialloc {bytes = 0; dbginfo = []}), args
  470.   | (Caddi, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Iadd args
  471.   | (Csubi, _) -> self#select_arith Isub args
  472.   | (Cmuli, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Imul args
  473.   | (Cmulhi, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Imulh args
  474.   | (Cdivi, _) -> (Iintop Idiv, args)
  475.   | (Cmodi, _) -> (Iintop Imod, args)
  476.   | (Cand, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Iand args
  477.   | (Cor, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Ior args
  478.   | (Cxor, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Ixor args
  479.   | (Clsl, _) -> self#select_arith Ilsl args
  480.   | (Clsr, _) -> self#select_arith Ilsr args
  481.   | (Casr, _) -> self#select_arith Iasr args
  482.   | (Ccmpi comp, _) -> self#select_arith_comp (Isigned comp) args
  483.   | (Caddv, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Iadd args
  484.   | (Cadda, _) -> self#select_arith_comm Iadd args
  485.   | (Ccmpa comp, _) -> self#select_arith_comp (Iunsigned comp) args
  486.   | (Ccmpf comp, _) -> (Icompf comp, args)
  487.   | (Cnegf, _) -> (Inegf, args)
  488.   | (Cabsf, _) -> (Iabsf, args)
  489.   | (Caddf, _) -> (Iaddf, args)
  490.   | (Csubf, _) -> (Isubf, args)
  491.   | (Cmulf, _) -> (Imulf, args)
  492.   | (Cdivf, _) -> (Idivf, args)
  493.   | (Cfloatofint, _) -> (Ifloatofint, args)
  494.   | (Cintoffloat, _) -> (Iintoffloat, args)
  495.   | (Ccheckbound, _) ->
  496.     self#select_arith Icheckbound args
  497.   | _ -> Misc.fatal_error "Selection.select_oper"

  499. method private select_arith_comm op = function
  500.   | [arg; Cconst_int (n, _)] when self#is_immediate op n ->
  501.       (Iintop_imm(op, n), [arg])
  502.   | [Cconst_int (n, _); arg] when self#is_immediate op n ->
  503.       (Iintop_imm(op, n), [arg])
  504.   | args ->
  505.       (Iintop op, args)

  507. method private select_arith op = function
  508.   | [arg; Cconst_int (n, _)] when self#is_immediate op n ->
  509.       (Iintop_imm(op, n), [arg])
  510.   | args ->
  511.       (Iintop op, args)

  513. method private select_arith_comp cmp = function
  514.   | [arg; Cconst_int (n, _)] when self#is_immediate (Icomp cmp) n ->
  515.       (Iintop_imm(Icomp cmp, n), [arg])
  516.   | [Cconst_int (n, _); arg]
  517.     when self#is_immediate (Icomp(swap_intcomp cmp)) n ->
  518.       (Iintop_imm(Icomp(swap_intcomp cmp), n), [arg])
  519.   | args ->
  520.       (Iintop(Icomp cmp), args)

  522. (* Instruction selection for conditionals *)

  524. method select_condition = function
  525.   | Cop(Ccmpi cmp, [arg1; Cconst_int (n, _)], _)
  526.     when self#is_immediate_test (Isigned cmp) n ->
  527.       (Iinttest_imm(Isigned cmp, n), arg1)
  528.   | Cop(Ccmpi cmp, [Cconst_int (n, _); arg2], _)
  529.     when self#is_immediate_test (Isigned (swap_integer_comparison cmp)) n ->
  530.       (Iinttest_imm(Isigned(swap_integer_comparison cmp), n), arg2)
  531.   | Cop(Ccmpi cmp, args, _) ->
  532.       (Iinttest(Isigned cmp), Ctuple args)
  533.   | Cop(Ccmpa cmp, [arg1; Cconst_int (n, _)], _)
  534.     when self#is_immediate_test (Iunsigned cmp) n ->
  535.       (Iinttest_imm(Iunsigned cmp, n), arg1)
  536.   | Cop(Ccmpa cmp, [Cconst_int (n, _); arg2], _)
  537.     when self#is_immediate_test (Iunsigned (swap_integer_comparison cmp)) n ->
  538.       (Iinttest_imm(Iunsigned(swap_integer_comparison cmp), n), arg2)
  539.   | Cop(Ccmpa cmp, args, _) ->
  540.       (Iinttest(Iunsigned cmp), Ctuple args)
  541.   | Cop(Ccmpf cmp, args, _) ->
  542.       (Ifloattest cmp, Ctuple args)
  543.   | Cop(Cand, [arg; Cconst_int (1, _)], _) ->
  544.       (Ioddtest, arg)
  545.   | arg ->
  546.       (Itruetest, arg)

  548. (* Return an array of fresh registers of the given type.
  549.    Normally implemented as Reg.createv, but some
  550.    ports (e.g. Arm) can override this definition to store float values
  551.    in pairs of integer registers. *)

  553. method regs_for tys = Reg.createv tys

  555. (* Buffering of instruction sequences *)

  557. val mutable instr_seq = dummy_instr

  559. method insert_debug _env desc dbg arg res =
  560.   instr_seq <- instr_cons_debug desc arg res dbg instr_seq

  562. method insert _env desc arg res =
  563.   instr_seq <- instr_cons desc arg res instr_seq

  565. method extract_onto o =
  566.   let rec extract res i =
  567.     if i == dummy_instr
  568.       then res
  569.       else extract {i with next = res} i.next in
  570.     extract o instr_seq

  572. method extract =
  573.   self#extract_onto (end_instr ())

  575. (* Insert a sequence of moves from one pseudoreg set to another. *)

  577. method insert_move env src dst =
  578.   if src.stamp <> dst.stamp then
  579.     self#insert env (Iop Imove) [|src|] [|dst|]

  581. method insert_moves env src dst =
  582.   for i = 0 to Stdlib.Int.min (Array.length src) (Array.length dst) - 1 do
  583.     self#insert_move env src.(i) dst.(i)
  584.   done

  586. (* Insert moves and stack offsets for function arguments and results *)

  588. method insert_move_args env arg loc stacksize =
  589.   if stacksize <> 0 then begin
  590.     self#insert env (Iop(Istackoffset stacksize)) [||] [||]
  591.   end;
  592.   self#insert_moves env arg loc

  594. method insert_move_results env loc res stacksize =
  595.   if stacksize <> 0 then begin
  596.     self#insert env (Iop(Istackoffset(-stacksize))) [||] [||]
  597.   end;
  598.   self#insert_moves env loc res

  600. (* Add an Iop opcode. Can be overridden by processor description
  601.    to insert moves before and after the operation, i.e. for two-address
  602.    instructions, or instructions using dedicated registers. *)

  604. method insert_op_debug env op dbg rs rd =
  605.   self#insert_debug env (Iop op) dbg rs rd;
  606.   rd

  608. method insert_op env op rs rd =
  609.   self#insert_op_debug env op Debuginfo.none rs rd

  611. (* Add the instructions for the given expression
  612.    at the end of the self sequence *)

  614. method emit_expr (env:environment) exp =
  615.   match exp with
  616.     Cconst_int (n, _dbg) ->
  617.       let r = self#regs_for typ_int in
  618.       Some(self#insert_op env (Iconst_int(Nativeint.of_int n)) [||] r)
  619.   | Cconst_natint (n, _dbg) ->
  620.       let r = self#regs_for typ_int in
  621.       Some(self#insert_op env (Iconst_int n) [||] r)
  622.   | Cconst_float (n, _dbg) ->
  623.       let r = self#regs_for typ_float in
  624.       Some(self#insert_op env (Iconst_float (Int64.bits_of_float n)) [||] r)
  625.   | Cconst_symbol (n, _dbg) ->
  626.       (* Cconst_symbol _ evaluates to a statically-allocated address, so its
  627.          value fits in a typ_int register and is never changed by the GC.

  629.          Some Cconst_symbols point to statically-allocated blocks, some of
  630.          which may point to heap values. However, any such blocks will be
  631.          registered in the compilation unit's global roots structure, so
  632.          adding this register to the frame table would be redundant *)
  633.       let r = self#regs_for typ_int in
  634.       Some(self#insert_op env (Iconst_symbol n) [||] r)
  635.   | Cvar v ->
  636.       begin try
  637.         Some(env_find v env)
  638.       with Not_found ->
  639.         Misc.fatal_error("Selection.emit_expr: unbound var " ^ V.unique_name v)
  640.       end
  641.   | Clet(v, e1, e2) ->
  642.       begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  643.         None -> None
  644.       | Some r1 -> self#emit_expr (self#bind_let env v r1) e2
  645.       end
  646.   | Clet_mut(v, k, e1, e2) ->
  647.       begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  648.         None -> None
  649.       | Some r1 -> self#emit_expr (self#bind_let_mut env v k r1) e2
  650.       end
  651.   | Cphantom_let (_var, _defining_expr, body) ->
  652.       self#emit_expr env body
  653.   | Cassign(v, e1) ->
  654.       let rv =
  655.         try
  656.           env_find_mut v env
  657.         with Not_found ->
  658.           Misc.fatal_error ("Selection.emit_expr: unbound var " ^ V.name v) in
  659.       begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  660.         None -> None
  661.       | Some r1 ->
  662.           self#insert_moves env r1 rv; Some [||]
  663.       end
  664.   | Ctuple [] ->
  665.       Some [||]
  666.   | Ctuple exp_list ->
  667.       begin match self#emit_parts_list env exp_list with
  668.         None -> None
  669.       | Some(simple_list, ext_env) ->
  670.           Some(self#emit_tuple ext_env simple_list)
  671.       end
  672.   | Cop(Craise k, [arg], dbg) ->
  673.       begin match self#emit_expr env arg with
  674.         None -> None
  675.       | Some r1 ->
  676.           let rd = [|Proc.loc_exn_bucket|] in
  677.           self#insert env (Iop Imove) r1 rd;
  678.           self#insert_debug env  (Iraise k) dbg rd [||];
  679.           None
  680.       end
  681.   | Cop(Copaque, args, dbg) ->
  682.       begin match self#emit_parts_list env args with
  683.         None -> None
  684.       | Some (simple_args, env) ->
  685. ‌         let rs = self#emit_tuple env simple_args in
  686.          Some (self#insert_op_debug env Iopaque dbg rs rs)
  687.       end
  688.   | Cop(op, args, dbg) ->
  689.       begin match self#emit_parts_list env args with
  690.         None -> None
  691.       | Some(simple_args, env) ->
  692. ‌          let ty = oper_result_type op in
  693. ‌          let (new_op, new_args) = self#select_operation op simple_args dbg in
  694.           match new_op with
  695.             Icall_ind ->
  696. ‌              let r1 = self#emit_tuple env new_args in
  697. ‌              let rarg = Array.sub r1 1 (Array.length r1 - 1) in
  698. ‌              let rd = self#regs_for ty in
  699. ‌              let (loc_arg, stack_ofs) = Proc.loc_arguments (Reg.typv rarg) in
  700. ‌              let loc_res = Proc.loc_results (Reg.typv rd) in
  701.               self#insert_move_args env rarg loc_arg stack_ofs;
  702.               self#insert_debug env (Iop new_op) dbg
  703.                           (Array.append [|r1.(0)|] loc_arg) loc_res;
  704.               self#insert_move_results env loc_res rd stack_ofs;
  705.               Some rd
  706.           | Icall_imm _ ->
  707. ‌              let r1 = self#emit_tuple env new_args in
  708. ‌              let rd = self#regs_for ty in
  709. ‌              let (loc_arg, stack_ofs) = Proc.loc_arguments (Reg.typv r1) in
  710. ‌              let loc_res = Proc.loc_results (Reg.typv rd) in
  711.               self#insert_move_args env r1 loc_arg stack_ofs;
  712.               self#insert_debug env (Iop new_op) dbg loc_arg loc_res;
  713.               self#insert_move_results env loc_res rd stack_ofs;
  714.               Some rd
  715.           | Iextcall r ->
  716. ‌              let (loc_arg, stack_ofs) =
  717.                 self#emit_extcall_args env r.ty_args new_args in
  718. ‌              let rd = self#regs_for ty in
  719. ‌              let loc_res =
  720.                 self#insert_op_debug env
  721.                   (Iextcall {r with stack_ofs = stack_ofs}) dbg
  722.                   loc_arg (Proc.loc_external_results (Reg.typv rd)) in
  723.               self#insert_move_results env loc_res rd stack_ofs;
  724.               Some rd
  725.           | Ialloc { bytes = _; } ->
  726. ‌              let rd = self#regs_for typ_val in
  727. ‌              let bytes = size_expr env (Ctuple new_args) in
  728.               assert (bytes mod Arch.size_addr = 0);
  729. ‌              let alloc_words = bytes / Arch.size_addr in
  730. ‌              let op =
  731.                 Ialloc { bytes; dbginfo = [{alloc_words; alloc_dbg = dbg}] }
  732.               in
  733.               self#insert_debug env (Iop op) dbg [||] rd;
  734.               self#emit_stores env new_args rd;
  735.               Some rd
  736.           | op ->
  737. ‌              let r1 = self#emit_tuple env new_args in
  738. ‌              let rd = self#regs_for ty in
  739.               Some (self#insert_op_debug env op dbg r1 rd)
  740.       end
  741.   | Csequence(e1, e2) ->
  742.       begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  743.         None -> None
  744.       | Some _ -> self#emit_expr env e2
  745.       end
  746.   | Cifthenelse(econd, _ifso_dbg, eif, _ifnot_dbg, eelse, _dbg) ->
  747. ‌      let (cond, earg) = self#select_condition econd in
  748.       begin match self#emit_expr env earg with
  749.         None -> None
  750.       | Some rarg ->
  751. ‌          let (rif, sif) = self#emit_sequence env eif in
  752. ‌          let (relse, selse) = self#emit_sequence env eelse in
  753. ‌          let r = join env rif sif relse selse in
  754.           self#insert env (Iifthenelse(cond, sif#extract, selse#extract))
  755.                       rarg [||];
  756.           r
  757.       end
  758.   | Cswitch(esel, index, ecases, _dbg) ->
  759.       begin match self#emit_expr env esel with
  760.         None -> None
  761.       | Some rsel ->
  762. ‌          let rscases =
  763.             Array.map (fun (case, _dbg) -> self#emit_sequence env case) ecases
  764.           in
  765. ‌          let r = join_array env rscases in
  766.           self#insert env (Iswitch(index,
  767.                                    Array.map (fun (_, s) -> s#extract) rscases))
  768.                       rsel [||];
  769.           r
  770.       end
  771.   | Ccatch(_, [], e1) ->
  772.       self#emit_expr env e1
  773.   | Ccatch(rec_flag, handlers, body) ->
  774. ‌      let handlers =
  775.         List.map (fun (nfail, ids, e2, dbg) ->
  776.             let rs =
  777.               List.map
  778.                 (fun (id, typ) ->
  779.                   let r = self#regs_for typ in name_regs id r; r)
  780.                 ids in
  781.             (nfail, ids, rs, e2, dbg))
  782.           handlers
  783.       in
  784. ‌      let env =
  785.         (* Since the handlers may be recursive, and called from the body,
  786.            the same environment is used for translating both the handlers and
  787.            the body. *)
  788.         List.fold_left (fun env (nfail, _ids, rs, _e2, _dbg) ->
  789.             env_add_static_exception nfail rs env)
  790.           env handlers
  791.       in
  792. ‌      let (r_body, s_body) = self#emit_sequence env body in
  793. ‌      let translate_one_handler (nfail, ids, rs, e2, _dbg) =
  794.         assert(List.length ids = List.length rs);
  795.         let new_env =
  796.           List.fold_left (fun env ((id, _typ), r) -> env_add id r env)
  797.             env (List.combine ids rs)
  798.         in
  799.         let (r, s) = self#emit_sequence new_env e2 in
  800.         (nfail, (r, s))
  801.       in
  802. ‌      let l = List.map translate_one_handler handlers in
  803. ‌      let a = Array.of_list ((r_body, s_body) :: List.map snd l) in
  804. ‌      let r = join_array env a in
  805. ‌      let aux (nfail, (_r, s)) = (nfail, s#extract) in
  806.       self#insert env (Icatch (rec_flag, List.map aux l, s_body#extract))
  807.         [||] [||];
  808.       r
  809.   | Cexit (nfail,args) ->
  810.       begin match self#emit_parts_list env args with
  811.         None -> None
  812.       | Some (simple_list, ext_env) ->
  813. ‌          let src = self#emit_tuple ext_env simple_list in
  814. ‌          let dest_args =
  815.             try env_find_static_exception nfail env
  816.             with Not_found ->
  817.               Misc.fatal_error ("Selection.emit_expr: unbound label "^
  818.                                 Stdlib.Int.to_string nfail)
  819.           in
  820.           (* Intermediate registers to handle cases where some
  821.              registers from src are present in dest *)
  822. ‌          let tmp_regs = Reg.createv_like src in
  823.           (* Ccatch registers must not contain out of heap pointers *)
  824.           Array.iter (fun reg -> assert(reg.typ <> Addr)) src;
  825.           self#insert_moves env src tmp_regs ;
  826.           self#insert_moves env tmp_regs (Array.concat dest_args) ;
  827.           self#insert env (Iexit nfail) [||] [||];
  828.           None
  829.       end
  830.   | Ctrywith(e1, v, e2, _dbg) ->
  831. ‌      let (r1, s1) = self#emit_sequence env e1 in
  832. ‌      let rv = self#regs_for typ_val in
  833. ‌      let (r2, s2) = self#emit_sequence (env_add v rv env) e2 in
  834. ‌      let r = join env r1 s1 r2 s2 in
  835.       self#insert env
  836.         (Itrywith(s1#extract,
  837.                   instr_cons (Iop Imove) [|Proc.loc_exn_bucket|] rv
  838.                              (s2#extract)))
  839.         [||] [||];
  840.       r

  842. method private emit_sequence (env:environment) exp =
  843.   let s = {< instr_seq = dummy_instr >} in
  844.   let r = s#emit_expr env exp in
  845.   (r, s)

  847. method private bind_let (env:environment) v r1 =
  848.   if all_regs_anonymous r1 then begin
  849.     name_regs v r1;
  850.     env_add v r1 env
  851.   end else begin
  852.     let rv = Reg.createv_like r1 in
  853.     name_regs v rv;
  854.     self#insert_moves env r1 rv;
  855.     env_add v rv env
  856.   end

  858. method private bind_let_mut (env:environment) v k r1 =
  859.   let rv = self#regs_for k in
  860.   name_regs v rv;
  861.   self#insert_moves env r1 rv;
  862.   env_add ~mut:Mutable v rv env

  864. (* The following two functions, [emit_parts] and [emit_parts_list], force
  865.    right-to-left evaluation order as required by the Flambda [Un_anf] pass
  866.    (and to be consistent with the bytecode compiler). *)

  868. method private emit_parts (env:environment) ~effects_after exp =
  869.   let module EC = Effect_and_coeffect in
  870. ‌  let may_defer_evaluation =
  871.     let ec = self#effects_of exp in
  872.     match EC.effect ec with
  873.     | Effect.Arbitrary | Effect.Raise ->
  874.       (* Preserve the ordering of effectful expressions by evaluating them
  875.          early (in the correct order) and assigning their results to
  876.          temporaries.  We can avoid this in just one case: if we know that
  877.          every [exp'] in the original expression list (cf. [emit_parts_list])
  878.          to be evaluated after [exp] cannot possibly affect the result of
  879.          [exp] or depend on the result of [exp], then [exp] may be deferred.
  880.          (Checking purity here is not enough: we need to check copurity too
  881.          to avoid e.g. moving mutable reads earlier than the raising of
  882.          an exception.) *)
  883.       EC.pure_and_copure effects_after
  884.     | Effect.None ->
  885.       match EC.coeffect ec with
  886.       | Coeffect.None ->
  887.         (* Pure expressions may be moved. *)
  888.         true
  889.       | Coeffect.Read_mutable -> begin
  890.         (* Read-mutable expressions may only be deferred if evaluation of
  891.            every [exp'] (for [exp'] as in the comment above) has no effects
  892.            "worse" (in the sense of the ordering in [Effect.t]) than raising
  893.            an exception. *)
  894.         match EC.effect effects_after with
  895.         | Effect.None | Effect.Raise -> true
  896.         | Effect.Arbitrary -> false
  897.       end
  898.       | Coeffect.Arbitrary -> begin
  899.         (* Arbitrary expressions may only be deferred if evaluation of
  900.            every [exp'] (for [exp'] as in the comment above) has no effects. *)
  901.         match EC.effect effects_after with
  902.         | Effect.None -> true
  903.         | Effect.Arbitrary | Effect.Raise -> false
  904.       end
  905.   in
  906.   (* Even though some expressions may look like they can be deferred from
  907.      the (co)effect analysis, it may be forbidden to move them. *)
  908.   if may_defer_evaluation && self#is_simple_expr exp then
  909.     Some (exp, env)
  910.   else begin
  911.     match self#emit_expr env exp with
  912.       None -> None
  913.     | Some r ->
  914.         if Array.length r = 0 then
  915.           Some (Ctuple [], env)
  916.         else begin
  917.           (* The normal case *)
  918. ‌          let id = V.create_local "bind" in
  919.           if all_regs_anonymous r then
  920.             (* r is an anonymous, unshared register; use it directly *)
  921.             Some (Cvar id, env_add (VP.create id) r env)
  922.           else begin
  923.             (* Introduce a fresh temp to hold the result *)
  924. ‌            let tmp = Reg.createv_like r in
  925.             self#insert_moves env r tmp;
  926.             Some (Cvar id, env_add (VP.create id) tmp env)
  927.           end
  928.         end
  929.   end

  931. method private emit_parts_list (env:environment) exp_list =
  932.   let module EC = Effect_and_coeffect in
  933. ‌  let exp_list_right_to_left, _effect =
  934.     (* Annotate each expression with the (co)effects that happen after it
  935.        when the original expression list is evaluated from right to left.
  936.        The resulting expression list has the rightmost expression first. *)
  937.     List.fold_left (fun (exp_list, effects_after) exp ->
  938.         let exp_effect = self#effects_of exp in
  939.         (exp, effects_after)::exp_list, EC.join exp_effect effects_after)
  940.       ([], EC.none)
  941.       exp_list
  942.   in
  943.   List.fold_left (fun results_and_env (exp, effects_after) ->
  944.       match results_and_env with
  945.       | None -> None
  946.       | Some (result, env) ->
  947.           match self#emit_parts env exp ~effects_after with
  948.           | None -> None
  949.           | Some (exp_result, env) -> Some (exp_result :: result, env))
  950.     (Some ([], env))
  951.     exp_list_right_to_left

  953. method private emit_tuple_not_flattened env exp_list =
  954.   let rec emit_list = function
  955.     [] -> []
  956.   | exp :: rem ->
  957.       (* Again, force right-to-left evaluation *)
  958.       let loc_rem = emit_list rem in
  959.       match self#emit_expr env exp with
  960.         None -> assert false  (* should have been caught in emit_parts *)
  961.       | Some loc_exp -> loc_exp :: loc_rem
  962.   in
  963.   emit_list exp_list

  965. method private emit_tuple env exp_list =
  966.   Array.concat (self#emit_tuple_not_flattened env exp_list)

  968. method emit_extcall_args env ty_args args =
  969.   let args = self#emit_tuple_not_flattened env args in
  970.   let ty_args =
  971.     if ty_args = [] then List.map (fun _ -> XInt) args else ty_args in
  972. ‌  let locs, stack_ofs = Proc.loc_external_arguments ty_args in
  973. ‌  let ty_args = Array.of_list ty_args in
  974.   if stack_ofs <> 0 then
  975.     self#insert env (Iop(Istackoffset stack_ofs)) [||] [||];
  976.   List.iteri
  977.     (fun i arg ->
  978.       self#insert_move_extcall_arg env ty_args.(i) arg locs.(i))
  979.     args;
  980.   Array.concat (Array.to_list locs), stack_ofs

  982. method insert_move_extcall_arg env _ty_arg src dst =
  983.   (* The default implementation is one or two ordinary moves.
  984.      (Two in the case of an int64 argument on a 32-bit platform.)
  985.      It can be overridden to use special move instructions,
  986.      for example a "32-bit move" instruction for int32 arguments. *)
  987.   self#insert_moves env src dst

  989. method emit_stores env data regs_addr =
  990.   let a =
  991.     ref (Arch.offset_addressing Arch.identity_addressing (-Arch.size_int)) in
  992.   List.iter
  993.     (fun e ->
  994.       let (op, arg) = self#select_store false !a e in
  995.       match self#emit_expr env arg with
  996.         None -> assert false
  997.       | Some regs ->
  998.           match op with
  999.             Istore(_, _, _) ->
  1000.               for i = 0 to Array.length regs - 1 do
  1001.                 let r = regs.(i) in
  1002.                 let kind = if r.typ = Float then Double else Word_val in
  1003.                 self#insert env
  1004.                             (Iop(Istore(kind, !a, false)))
  1005.                             (Array.append [|r|] regs_addr) [||];
  1006.                 a := Arch.offset_addressing !a (size_component r.typ)
  1007.               done
  1008.           | _ ->
  1009.               self#insert env (Iop op) (Array.append regs regs_addr) [||];
  1010.               a := Arch.offset_addressing !a (size_expr env e))
  1011.     data

  1013. (* Same, but in tail position *)

  1015. method private emit_return (env:environment) exp =
  1016.   match self#emit_expr env exp with
  1017.     None -> ()
  1018.   | Some r ->
  1019.       let loc = Proc.loc_results (Reg.typv r) in
  1020.       self#insert_moves env r loc;
  1021.       self#insert env Ireturn loc [||]

  1023. method emit_tail (env:environment) exp =
  1024.   match exp with
  1025.     Clet(v, e1, e2) ->
  1026.       begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  1027.         None -> ()
  1028.       | Some r1 -> self#emit_tail (self#bind_let env v r1) e2
  1029.       end
  1030.   | Clet_mut (v, k, e1, e2) ->
  1031.      begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  1032.        None -> ()
  1033.      | Some r1 -> self#emit_tail (self#bind_let_mut env v k r1) e2
  1034.      end
  1035.   | Cphantom_let (_var, _defining_expr, body) ->
  1036.       self#emit_tail env body
  1037.   | Cop((Capply ty) as op, args, dbg) ->
  1038.       begin match self#emit_parts_list env args with
  1039.         None -> ()
  1040.       | Some(simple_args, env) ->
  1041.           let (new_op, new_args) = self#select_operation op simple_args dbg in
  1042.           match new_op with
  1043.             Icall_ind ->
  1044.               let r1 = self#emit_tuple env new_args in
  1045.               let rarg = Array.sub r1 1 (Array.length r1 - 1) in
  1046.               let (loc_arg, stack_ofs) = Proc.loc_arguments (Reg.typv rarg) in
  1047.               if stack_ofs = 0 then begin
  1048.                 let call = Iop (Itailcall_ind) in
  1049.                 self#insert_moves env rarg loc_arg;
  1050.                 self#insert_debug env call dbg
  1051.                             (Array.append [|r1.(0)|] loc_arg) [||];
  1052.               end else begin
  1053.                 let rd = self#regs_for ty in
  1054.                 let loc_res = Proc.loc_results (Reg.typv rd) in
  1055.                 self#insert_move_args env rarg loc_arg stack_ofs;
  1056.                 self#insert_debug env (Iop new_op) dbg
  1057.                             (Array.append [|r1.(0)|] loc_arg) loc_res;
  1058.                 self#insert env (Iop(Istackoffset(-stack_ofs))) [||] [||];
  1059.                 self#insert env Ireturn loc_res [||]
  1060.               end
  1061.           | Icall_imm { func; } ->
  1062. ‌              let r1 = self#emit_tuple env new_args in
  1063. ‌              let (loc_arg, stack_ofs) = Proc.loc_arguments (Reg.typv r1) in
  1064.               if stack_ofs = 0 then begin
  1065. ‌                let call = Iop (Itailcall_imm { func; }) in
  1066.                 self#insert_moves env r1 loc_arg;
  1067.                 self#insert_debug env call dbg loc_arg [||];
  1068.               end else if func = !current_function_name then begin
  1069. ‌                let call = Iop (Itailcall_imm { func; }) in
  1070. ‌                let loc_arg' = Proc.loc_parameters (Reg.typv r1) in
  1071.                 self#insert_moves env r1 loc_arg';
  1072.                 self#insert_debug env call dbg loc_arg' [||];
  1073.               end else begin
  1074. ‌                let rd = self#regs_for ty in
  1075. ‌                let loc_res = Proc.loc_results (Reg.typv rd) in
  1076.                 self#insert_move_args env r1 loc_arg stack_ofs;
  1077.                 self#insert_debug env (Iop new_op) dbg loc_arg loc_res;
  1078.                 self#insert env (Iop(Istackoffset(-stack_ofs))) [||] [||];
  1079.                 self#insert env Ireturn loc_res [||]
  1080.               end
  1081.           | _ -> Misc.fatal_error "Selection.emit_tail"
  1082.       end
  1083.   | Csequence(e1, e2) ->
  1084.       begin match self#emit_expr env e1 with
  1085.         None -> ()
  1086.       | Some _ -> self#emit_tail env e2
  1087.       end
  1088.   | Cifthenelse(econd, _ifso_dbg, eif, _ifnot_dbg, eelse, _dbg) ->
  1089. ‌      let (cond, earg) = self#select_condition econd in
  1090.       begin match self#emit_expr env earg with
  1091.         None -> ()
  1092.       | Some rarg ->
  1093.           self#insert env
  1094.                       (Iifthenelse(cond, self#emit_tail_sequence env eif,
  1095.                                          self#emit_tail_sequence env eelse))
  1096.                       rarg [||]
  1097.       end
  1098.   | Cswitch(esel, index, ecases, _dbg) ->
  1099.       begin match self#emit_expr env esel with
  1100.         None -> ()
  1101.       | Some rsel ->
  1102. ‌          let cases =
  1103.             Array.map (fun (case, _dbg) -> self#emit_tail_sequence env case)
  1104.               ecases
  1105.           in
  1106.           self#insert env (Iswitch (index, cases)) rsel [||]
  1107.       end
  1108.   | Ccatch(_, [], e1) ->
  1109.       self#emit_tail env e1
  1110.   | Ccatch(rec_flag, handlers, e1) ->
  1111. ‌      let handlers =
  1112.         List.map (fun (nfail, ids, e2, dbg) ->
  1113.             let rs =
  1114.               List.map
  1115.                 (fun (id, typ) ->
  1116.                   let r = self#regs_for typ in name_regs id r; r)
  1117.                 ids in
  1118.             (nfail, ids, rs, e2, dbg))
  1119.           handlers in
  1120. ‌      let env =
  1121.         List.fold_left (fun env (nfail, _ids, rs, _e2, _dbg) ->
  1122.             env_add_static_exception nfail rs env)
  1123.           env handlers in
  1124. ‌      let s_body = self#emit_tail_sequence env e1 in
  1125. ‌      let aux (nfail, ids, rs, e2, _dbg) =
  1126.         assert(List.length ids = List.length rs);
  1127.         let new_env =
  1128.           List.fold_left
  1129.             (fun env ((id, _typ),r) -> env_add id r env)
  1130.             env (List.combine ids rs) in
  1131.         nfail, self#emit_tail_sequence new_env e2
  1132.       in
  1133.       self#insert env (Icatch(rec_flag, List.map aux handlers, s_body))
  1134.         [||] [||]
  1135.   | Ctrywith(e1, v, e2, _dbg) ->
  1136. ‌      let (opt_r1, s1) = self#emit_sequence env e1 in
  1137. ‌      let rv = self#regs_for typ_val in
  1138. ‌      let s2 = self#emit_tail_sequence (env_add v rv env) e2 in
  1139.       self#insert env
  1140.         (Itrywith(s1#extract,
  1141.                   instr_cons (Iop Imove) [|Proc.loc_exn_bucket|] rv s2))
  1142.         [||] [||];
  1143.       begin match opt_r1 with
  1144.         None -> ()
  1145.       | Some r1 ->
  1146. ‌          let loc = Proc.loc_results (Reg.typv r1) in
  1147.           self#insert_moves env r1 loc;
  1148.           self#insert env Ireturn loc [||]
  1149.       end
  1150.   | Cop _
  1151.   | Cconst_int _ | Cconst_natint _ | Cconst_float _ | Cconst_symbol _
  1152.   | Cvar _
  1153.   | Cassign _
  1154.   | Ctuple _
  1155.   | Cexit _ ->
  1156.     self#emit_return env exp

  1158. method private emit_tail_sequence env exp =
  1159.   let s = {< instr_seq = dummy_instr >} in
  1160.   s#emit_tail env exp;
  1161.   s#extract

  1163. (* Sequentialization of a function definition *)

  1165. method emit_fundecl ~future_funcnames f =
  1166.   current_function_name := f.Cmm.fun_name;
  1167.   let rargs =
  1168.     List.map
  1169.       (fun (id, ty) -> let r = self#regs_for ty in name_regs id r; r)
  1170.       f.Cmm.fun_args in
  1171.   let rarg = Array.concat rargs in
  1172.   let loc_arg = Proc.loc_parameters (Reg.typv rarg) in
  1173.   let env =
  1174.     List.fold_right2
  1175.       (fun (id, _ty) r env -> env_add id r env)
  1176.       f.Cmm.fun_args rargs env_empty in
  1177.   self#emit_tail env f.Cmm.fun_body;
  1178.   let body = self#extract in
  1179.   instr_seq <- dummy_instr;
  1180.   self#insert_moves env loc_arg rarg;
  1181.   let polled_body =
  1182.     if Polling.requires_prologue_poll ~future_funcnames
  1183.          ~fun_name:f.Cmm.fun_name body
  1184.       then
  1185.         instr_cons_debug
  1186.           (Iop(Ipoll { return_label = None })) [||] [||] f.Cmm.fun_dbg body
  1187.     else
  1188.       body
  1189.     in
  1190. ‌  let body_with_prologue = self#extract_onto polled_body in
  1191.   instr_iter (fun instr -> self#mark_instr instr.Mach.desc) body_with_prologue;
  1192.   { fun_name = f.Cmm.fun_name;
  1193.     fun_args = loc_arg;
  1194.     fun_body = body_with_prologue;
  1195.     fun_codegen_options = f.Cmm.fun_codegen_options;
  1196.     fun_dbg  = f.Cmm.fun_dbg;
  1197.     fun_poll = f.Cmm.fun_poll;
  1198.     fun_num_stack_slots = Array.make Proc.num_register_classes 0;
  1199.     fun_contains_calls = !contains_calls;
  1200.   }

  1202. end

  1204. ‌let reset () =
  1205.   current_function_name := ""
